        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 4:18PM MDT by NWS Riverton WY</headline>
        <description>At 418 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 14 miles southwest of Crooks Gap, which is 22 miles
southwest of Jeffrey City, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern
Fremont and northeastern Sweetwater Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
